### Linbik OAuth 2.0 Test Scenarios
### Base URL
@linbik_base = https://localhost:5001
@aspnet_base = https://localhost:7020

### Variables (REPLACE THESE WITH YOUR ACTUAL VALUES)
@service_id = YOUR_SERVICE_ID_HERE
@api_key = YOUR_API_KEY_HERE

### ============================================
### Scenario 1: Simple OAuth Flow (Manual)
### ============================================

### Step 1.1: Open authorization URL in browser
### Copy this URL and open in your browser:
### {{linbik_base}}/auth/{{service_id}}

### Step 1.2: After callback, view token info
GET {{aspnet_base}}/oauth/token-info
Accept: application/json

### ============================================
### Scenario 2: PKCE Flow (Automated)
### ============================================

### Step 2.1: Generate PKCE parameters
GET {{aspnet_base}}/pkce/generate
Accept: application/json

### Step 2.2: Start PKCE flow
GET {{aspnet_base}}/pkce/start?state=my-custom-state
Accept: application/json

### Response will contain:
### - sessionId (save this)
### - authorizationUrl (open in browser)
### - codeVerifier (for reference)

### Step 2.3: After callback, validate PKCE
### Replace @session_id and @auth_code with actual values from callback
@session_id = SESSION_ID_FROM_STEP_2.2
@auth_code = AUTH_CODE_FROM_CALLBACK

POST {{aspnet_base}}/pkce/validate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sessionId": "{{session_id}}",
  "authorizationCode": "{{auth_code}}"
}

### ============================================
### Scenario 3: Token Management
### ============================================

### View current token information
GET {{aspnet_base}}/oauth/token-info
Accept: application/json

### Refresh tokens
POST {{aspnet_base}}/oauth/test-refresh
Content-Type: application/json

### Clear token cache
POST {{aspnet_base}}/oauth/clear-cache
Content-Type: application/json

### ============================================
### Scenario 4: Integration Service Testing
### ============================================

### Test integration service call
@service_package = payment-gateway

POST {{aspnet_base}}/oauth/test-integration/{{service_package}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 1000,
  "currency": "TRY",
  "description": "Test payment"
}

### ============================================
### Scenario 5: Authorization URL Building
### ============================================

### Simple authorization URL (no PKCE)
### {{linbik_base}}/auth/{{service_id}}

### Authorization URL with state
### {{linbik_base}}/auth/{{service_id}}?user_session_code=my-state-123

### Authorization URL with PKCE (use code challenge from /pkce/generate)
@code_challenge = GENERATED_CODE_CHALLENGE_HERE
### {{linbik_base}}/auth/{{service_id}}/{{code_challenge}}

### Authorization URL with PKCE + state
### {{linbik_base}}/auth/{{service_id}}/{{code_challenge}}?user_session_code=my-state-123

### ============================================
### Scenario 6: Direct Token Exchange (Advanced)
### ============================================

### This is what happens behind the scenes in /oauth/callback
@authorization_code = YOUR_AUTH_CODE_HERE

POST {{linbik_base}}/oauth/token
ApiKey: {{api_key}}
Code: {{authorization_code}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### ============================================
### Scenario 7: Refresh Token Flow (Direct)
### ============================================

@refresh_token = YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE

POST {{linbik_base}}/oauth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refresh_token}}",
  "apiKey": "{{api_key}}",
  "communityId": "{{service_id}}"
}

### ============================================
### Scenario 8: PKCE Cleanup
### ============================================

### Clear stored PKCE code verifiers
POST {{aspnet_base}}/pkce/clear
Content-Type: application/json

### ============================================
### Quick Test Checklist
### ============================================

### ✅ 1. Configure variables at top of file
### ✅ 2. Start Linbik.App (port 5001)
### ✅ 3. Create service in Linbik.App
### ✅ 4. Update @service_id and @api_key
### ✅ 5. Start AspNet.Examples (port 7020)
### ✅ 6. Run Scenario 1 or 2
### ✅ 7. Check /oauth/token-info
### ✅ 8. Test refresh with Scenario 3
### ✅ 9. Test integration services (if configured)

